<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,761,525,1029]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,525,548]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elongate species, with oval head, conspicuously setose latero-basal impressions of pronotum distinct, and elytral setation somewhat modified. Mesoventrite with partly bordered lateral margins (sulcus reduced laterally), with indication of longitudinal submedian carinae; setose fringe of mesepimera well-developed; submarginal setose impressions of metaventrite and abdominal sternum III conspicuous; all tibiae with paired terminal spurs; elytral apices in males distinctly modified, with peculiar sinuate longitudinal sulcus near middle (
<figureCitation box="[493,583,813,836]" captionStart="Figs 138–150. 138–147" captionStartId="53.[150,187,1961,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,491,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@53.[173,1412,489,1951]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 138–150. 138–147 – Habitus: 138 – Microhoria ocreata (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1847) comb. nov.; 139 – M. oedipus (Chevrolat, 1860); 140 – M. olivacea (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1849) comb. nov.; 141 – M. paupercula (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1849) comb. nov.; 142 – M. babaulti (Pic, 1921) comb. nov.; 143 – M. cervi sp. nov.; 144 – M. sulaimanica sp. nov., paratype; 145 – M. terminata (W. L. E. Schmidt, 1842); 146 – M. anahita sp. nov.; 147 – M. angelinii (Degiovanni, 2012) comb. nov.; 148 – M. apicordiger (Bonadona, 1958) comb. nov., apex of elytra; 150 – M. gibbipennis sp. nov., apex of elytra; 150 – M. angelinii, apex of female tergum VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3880277" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3880277/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 82–84" captionStartId="31.[155,192,2035,2054]" captionTargetBox="[275,1326,1082,2014]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[249,1339,1070,2025]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figs 82–84. Aedeagus: 82 – Microhoria apicordiger (Bonadona, 1954) comb. nov. in ventral (left) and lateral (right) view; 83 – M. henoni (Pic, 1892) comb. nov., ventral view; 84 – same, apical part, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm – A (Figs 83, 84), B (Fig. 82)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3880251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3880251/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
): tegmen capsuliform, bilobed apically; gonopore free. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,877,900]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Distribution.</emphasis>
Northern Africa (
<collectingCountry box="[487,590,877,900]" name="Morocco" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Morocco</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,761,525,1029]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,909,932]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Species included</emphasis>
(4 spp.). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bonadona, 1954)" authorityName="Kejval &amp; Chandler" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Bonadona" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicordiger" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[447,702,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Microhoria apicordiger</emphasis>
(Bonadona, 1954)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[312,433,941,964]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[444,560,941,965]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">M. kocheri</emphasis>
(Pic, 1951) comb. nov., 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1936)" authorityName="Kejval &amp; Chandler" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[214,530,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plicatipennis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[214,395,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">M. plicatipennis</emphasis>
(Pic, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,667,973,996]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">M. postimpressa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PIC M." box="[305,409,1005,1028]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" pagination="9 - 11" refId="ref55663" refString="PIC M. 1938: Notes diverses, nouveautes (Suite). L'Echange, Revue Linneenne 54: 9 - 11." type="journal article" year="1938">Pic, 1938</bibRefCitation>
) comb. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="126" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[828,1437,190,437]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,938,190,213]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Remarks.</emphasis>
All four species of this group were previously placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1894" box="[930,1056,222,245]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Clavicomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[930,1056,222,245]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Clavicomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CHANDLER D. S. &amp; UHMANN G. &amp; NARDI G. &amp; TELNOV D." box="[1070,1298,222,245]" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" pagination="421 - 455" refId="ref52747" refString="CHANDLER D. S., UHMANN G., NARDI G. &amp; TELNOV D. 2008: Family Anthicidae Latreille, 1819. Pp. 421 - 455. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 670 pp." type="book chapter" year="2008">CHANDLER et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Clavicollis</emphasis>
). They share nearly all characters of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kejval &amp; Chandler" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1300,1436,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schimperi">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">A. schimperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group, but differ by the peculiar modification of the male elytra (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1109,318,341]" captionStart="Figs 138–150. 138–147" captionStartId="53.[150,187,1961,1980]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,491,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@53.[173,1412,489,1951]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="Figs 138–150. 138–147 – Habitus: 138 – Microhoria ocreata (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1847) comb. nov.; 139 – M. oedipus (Chevrolat, 1860); 140 – M. olivacea (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1849) comb. nov.; 141 – M. paupercula (LaFerté-Sénectère, 1849) comb. nov.; 142 – M. babaulti (Pic, 1921) comb. nov.; 143 – M. cervi sp. nov.; 144 – M. sulaimanica sp. nov., paratype; 145 – M. terminata (W. L. E. Schmidt, 1842); 146 – M. anahita sp. nov.; 147 – M. angelinii (Degiovanni, 2012) comb. nov.; 148 – M. apicordiger (Bonadona, 1958) comb. nov., apex of elytra; 150 – M. gibbipennis sp. nov., apex of elytra; 150 – M. angelinii, apex of female tergum VII." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3880277" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3880277/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
). Species-group placement of 
<emphasis box="[828,946,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="126">M. kocheri</emphasis>
is tentative, based on relationships noted in the original description (described from a single female specimen).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
